Description: HCR is a wealth management firm dedicated to providing financial and investment strategies to their clients.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: At HCR Wealth Advisors, we understand the magnitude of life’s biggest moments. No matter where a client might be in their financial journey, or what life decision they are making, we are here to guide them and stand by their side in challenging times and times of prosperity.  Our clients trust and rely on us for personalized service and to make critical decisions for them and their financial well-being. We feel it is our duty and privilege to educate and empower our clients, and to provide confidence and financial understanding. We believe in doing what is right for every individual we serve so we work to build deep connections with our clients and work with them to overcome challenges that may be standing in the way of their ideal financial outcome.  Exceptional client service is at the heart of who we are. We pride ourselves on providing comprehensive financial advice, developing and refining investment strategies, and ensuring our clients are organized and on track to meet their goals.  HCR is not your average financial advisor and we refuse to be influenced by any consideration beyond the needs of our clients and their families. To maintain objectivity and integrity, we follow four important, self-imposed rules:  1)	We do not accept commissions from mutual fund companies or money managers and  2)	We do provide proprietary strategies, but we do not employ the use of proprietary products 3)	We use an advisory model that allows our guidance to be totally agnostic 4)	All of our clients’ accounts reside at SIPC-insured institutions We take a holistic advisory approach by factoring in specific lifestyle and personal considerations to map out a client’s financial life so they can reach those goals as simply and painlessly as possible.  Our clients trust us to make critical decisions and provide unmatched personalized service to each and every one of them. At HCR Wealth Advisors, we do just that.

Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Castro Theatre is a San Francisco-based movie palace built by two theatre entrepreneurs, the Nasser brothers. It is one of the few remaining movie palaces in the nation from the 1920s, which is still in operation. The theatre’s designer was Timothy L. Pflueger who went on to become a famous Bay Area architect. He chose an exterior design reminiscent of a Mexican cathedral. The large windows, shape of the roof line of the front wall of the building, and plaster wall decorations all combine to convey a look of grandeur in keeping with the large scale of many theatres built in the 1920s. The marquee and vertical neon sign are additions from the late 1930s, but the glazed tile street foyer, ornate tent-like box office, and the wooden doors are all from the early 1920s. Castro Theatre’s interior is very diverse. One can sense Spanish, Oriental, and Italian influences. The auditorium seats over 1400 in an intimate setting. On either side of the stage and screen are large organ grills. The Art Deco chandelier date...

Full Description: HIPAA stands for the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA). It is commonly misspelled as “HIPPA” when individuals have not taken training or completed HIPAA compliance initiative. It is a federal law passed in 1996 as an attempt at incremental healthcare reform. It was revised in 2009 with the ARRA/HITECH Act, meaningful use, in 2013 with the Omnibus Rule and additional minor changes. HIPAA regulation’s goal is to reform the healthcare and Insurance industries by reducing paperwork & costs, simplifying administrative processes, burdens and improving the privacy and security of patients’ information with easy accessibility of their records.
